---
import MainLayout from "../components/MainLayout.astro";
import { getEntryByCanonicalPath } from "../utils/contentCollections";
import { extractFaqItemsFromMarkdown } from "../utils/faq";
import { buildFaqPageSchema } from "../utils/schema";

const canonicalPath = "/";
const entry = await getEntryByCanonicalPath("pages", canonicalPath);
const faqItems = extractFaqItemsFromMarkdown(entry.body);
const faqSchema = buildFaqPageSchema({ canonicalPath, items: faqItems });
const schema = faqSchema ? [faqSchema] : [];
---

<MainLayout
  title={entry.data.title}
  summary={entry.data.summary}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  schema={schema}
  showBreadcrumbs={false}
  showLocalSubnav={false}
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hp-hero">
    <div class="hp-container hp-hero-inner">
      <h1 class="hp-headline">Decision-Grade Research for AI, Robotics, and Industrial Automation Markets</h1>
      <p class="hp-sub">Autonomy Bridge is a principal-led boutique research firm. The firm produces decision-grade research for vendors, investors, and operators in AI, robotics, and industrial automation markets.</p>
      <p class="hp-sub">Engagements are commissioned before capital is committed or reputation is staked. The output is a decision brief ,  explicit assumptions, structured models, and direct recommendations.</p>
      <div class="hp-hero-ctas">
        <a href="/advisory" class="hp-btn-primary">Advisory →</a>
        <a href="/bespoke-research" class="hp-btn-outline">Bespoke Research →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT WE DO -->
  <section class="hp-section">
    <div class="hp-container">
      <h2 class="hp-section-heading">What We Do</h2>
      <p class="hp-section-sub">Every engagement addresses one of four decision problems.</p>
      <div class="hp-decision-grid">
        <div class="hp-decision-card">
          <span class="hp-decision-label">Commercial viability</span>
          <p>Is this market real, and is it real for this product at this stage? Autonomy Bridge maps the buyer population, tests demand assumptions against operator economics, and identifies where unit economics hold and where they break.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hp-decision-card">
          <span class="hp-decision-label">Opportunity sizing</span>
          <p>How large is the addressable market, defined by realistic buyer criteria rather than top-down TAM estimates? Engagements produce a bottom-up count of qualified accounts with revenue potential and prioritization logic.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hp-decision-card">
          <span class="hp-decision-label">ICP definition</span>
          <p>Which buyers are genuinely reachable, fundable, and closeable given current product maturity, pricing, and sales motion? The output is a defined ideal customer profile with qualifying and disqualifying conditions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hp-decision-card">
          <span class="hp-decision-label">Pricing and go-to-market direction</span>
          <p>What pricing structure do comparable operators accept, what does the competitive set charge, and what GTM motion fits the buyer's procurement process?</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="hp-decision-footer">These are pre-commitment questions. Autonomy Bridge builds the evidence base to answer them before the commitment is made.</p>
      <div class="hp-section-links">
        <a href="/frameworks" class="hp-text-link">Frameworks →</a>
        <a href="/methodology" class="hp-text-link">Methodology →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHO THIS IS FOR -->
  <section class="hp-section hp-section--surface">
    <div class="hp-container">
      <h2 class="hp-section-heading">Who This Is For</h2>
      <div class="hp-audience-grid">
        <div class="hp-audience-card">
          <span class="hp-audience-type">Robotics and AI vendors</span>
          <p>Evaluating whether a new segment or geography is worth entering, what pricing the market will support, and which buyers to target first.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hp-audience-card">
          <span class="hp-audience-type">Investors</span>
          <p>Conducting due diligence on a robotics or automation company ,  sizing the addressable market, assessing vendor economics, and stress-testing deployment assumptions before writing a check.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hp-audience-card">
          <span class="hp-audience-type">Operators</span>
          <p>Evaluating whether automation makes economic sense for their environment, which vendors to shortlist, and what contract terms to negotiate.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="hp-audience-footer">Each actor type faces a different version of the same problem: a high-stakes decision with incomplete information and real consequences for being wrong.</p>
      <div class="hp-section-links">
        <a href="/advisory" class="hp-text-link">Advisory →</a>
        <a href="/bespoke-research" class="hp-text-link">Bespoke Research →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FRAMEWORKS -->
  <section class="hp-section">
    <div class="hp-container">
      <h2 class="hp-section-heading">Proprietary Frameworks</h2>
      <p class="hp-section-sub">Seven proprietary analytical frameworks applied across all engagements. Each framework was built to structure a specific class of decision problem in AI, robotics, and industrial automation markets.</p>
      <div class="hp-fw-grid">
        <a href="/frameworks/robotics-roi-model" class="hp-fw-card">
          <span class="hp-fw-type">Economic model</span>
          <span class="hp-fw-name">Robotics ROI Model</span>
          <span class="hp-fw-desc">Capital recovery, utilization thresholds, and payback conditions for robotics deployments</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/frameworks/automation-failure-framework" class="hp-fw-card">
          <span class="hp-fw-type">Failure taxonomy</span>
          <span class="hp-fw-name">Automation Failure Framework</span>
          <span class="hp-fw-desc">Structural failure modes that prevent automation from reaching production economics</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/frameworks/warehouse-automation-decision-framework" class="hp-fw-card">
          <span class="hp-fw-type">Decision model</span>
          <span class="hp-fw-name">Warehouse Automation Decision Framework</span>
          <span class="hp-fw-desc">Decision criteria for evaluating automation readiness and sequencing deployment</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/frameworks/pilot-to-scale-failure-framework" class="hp-fw-card">
          <span class="hp-fw-type">Risk analysis</span>
          <span class="hp-fw-name">Pilot-to-Scale Failure Framework</span>
          <span class="hp-fw-desc">Why pilots succeed and full deployments fail, and the conditions that predict each outcome</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/frameworks/vendor-economics-framework" class="hp-fw-card">
          <span class="hp-fw-type">Pricing model</span>
          <span class="hp-fw-name">Vendor Economics Framework</span>
          <span class="hp-fw-desc">How robotics and automation vendors structure their economics, and what that means for buyers and investors</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/frameworks/vendor-evaluation-framework" class="hp-fw-card">
          <span class="hp-fw-type">Scoring model</span>
          <span class="hp-fw-name">Vendor Evaluation Framework</span>
          <span class="hp-fw-desc">Criteria and scoring methodology for shortlisting and selecting automation vendors</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/frameworks/workflow-architecture-framework" class="hp-fw-card">
          <span class="hp-fw-type">Design mapping</span>
          <span class="hp-fw-name">Workflow Architecture Framework</span>
          <span class="hp-fw-desc">How workflow structure determines automation compatibility and deployment sequencing</span>
        </a>
      </div>
      <a href="/frameworks" class="hp-view-all">View all frameworks →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  {faqItems.length > 0 && (
    <section class="hp-section hp-section--surface">
      <div class="hp-container hp-faq-container">
        <h2 class="hp-section-heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="hp-faq-list">
          {faqItems.map((item) => (
            <details class="hp-faq-item">
              <summary class="hp-faq-q">{item.question}</summary>
              <p class="hp-faq-a">{item.answer}</p>
            </details>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  )}

  <!-- TYPICAL OUTCOMES -->
  <section class="hp-section">
    <div class="hp-container">
      <h2 class="hp-section-heading">Typical Outcomes</h2>
      <p class="hp-section-sub">Representative outputs from prior Autonomy Bridge engagements.</p>
      <div class="hp-outcomes-list">
        <div class="hp-outcome">
          <p><strong>Produced a market entry brief</strong> for a robotics vendor entering the North American intralogistics segment ,  covering addressable operator count by tier, segment economics, competitive pricing benchmarks, and procurement decision criteria.</p>
          <cite class="hp-citation">Autonomy Bridge proprietary analysis, 2026</cite>
        </div>
        <div class="hp-outcome">
          <p><strong>Sized the addressable market</strong> for an autonomous inspection platform across energy infrastructure and commercial facilities operator domains ,  bottom-up account count with revenue potential by segment and deployment readiness scoring.</p>
          <cite class="hp-citation">Autonomy Bridge proprietary analysis, 2026</cite>
        </div>
        <div class="hp-outcome">
          <p><strong>Defined ICP and disqualifying conditions</strong> for an early-stage robotics vendor, reducing a 300-account prospect list to a 40-account prioritized target set based on operator economics, fleet size, and procurement cycle.</p>
          <cite class="hp-citation">Autonomy Bridge proprietary analysis, 2026</cite>
        </div>
        <div class="hp-outcome">
          <p><strong>Stress-tested deployment economics</strong> for an investor evaluating a Series B robotics company ,  identifying utilization assumptions, contract structure risks, and operator churn conditions not reflected in the company's financial model.</p>
          <cite class="hp-citation">Autonomy Bridge proprietary analysis, 2026</cite>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SERVICES CTA -->
  <section class="hp-cta-banner">
    <div class="hp-container hp-cta-inner">
      <div class="hp-cta-text">
        <h2 class="hp-cta-heading">Work with Autonomy Bridge</h2>
        <p class="hp-cta-sub">Two engagement types for vendors, investors, and operators requiring decision-grade analysis.</p>
        <ul class="hp-cta-services">
          <li><strong>Advisory</strong> ,  Retained engagement for ongoing market research, vendor evaluation, and investment analysis.</li>
          <li><strong>Bespoke Research</strong> ,  Scoped project to answer a specific market, ICP, or commercial viability question.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="hp-cta-entry">Engagements begin with a 15-minute scoping call.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hp-cta-actions">
        <a href="/contact" class="hp-btn-primary">Book 15-min call</a>
        <a href="/advisory" class="hp-btn-cta-outline">Advisory</a>
        <a href="/bespoke-research" class="hp-btn-cta-outline">Bespoke Research</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DECISION RESOURCES -->
  <section class="hp-section">
    <div class="hp-container">
      <h2 class="hp-section-heading">Decision Resources</h2>
      <div class="hp-resources-table-wrap">
        <table class="hp-resources-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Resource</th>
              <th>What You Will Find</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><a href="/frameworks">Frameworks</a></td>
              <td>7 proprietary analytical models for commercial viability, deployment economics, vendor evaluation, and go-to-market decisions in AI, robotics, and industrial automation</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><a href="/use-cases">Use Cases</a></td>
              <td>Applied analyses: ROI evaluation, deployment scenarios, vendor economics, ICP definition</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><a href="/case-studies">Case Studies</a></td>
              <td>Documented engagements with defined problem, approach, and output</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><a href="/insights">Insights</a></td>
              <td>Analytical articles on market structure, deployment economics, and vendor dynamics</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><a href="/market-overview">Market Overview</a></td>
              <td>Structured orientation across platform categories and operator domains in AI, robotics, and industrial automation</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><a href="/glossary">Glossary</a></td>
              <td>Precise definitions for terms across AI, robotics, and industrial automation ,  each linked to source frameworks</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  /* ── Layout helpers ── */
  .hp-container {
    max-width: 72rem;
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding-inline: 1.5rem;
  }

  /* ── HERO ── */
  .hp-hero {
    padding: 5rem 0 4.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
  }

  .hp-hero-inner {
    max-width: 52rem;
    margin-inline: auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .hp-headline {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: clamp(1.875rem, 1.4rem + 2vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .hp-sub {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    max-width: 46rem;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .hp-sub:last-of-type {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .hp-hero-ctas {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .hp-btn-outline {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.625rem 1.25rem;
    border: 1.5px solid var(--color-text-primary);
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.15s, color 0.15s;
  }

  .hp-btn-outline:hover {
    background: var(--color-text-primary);
    color: var(--color-cta-text);
  }

  .hp-btn-primary {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.625rem 1.25rem;
    background: var(--color-cta-bg);
    border: 1.5px solid var(--color-cta-border);
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-cta-text);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.15s, border-color 0.15s;
  }

  .hp-btn-primary:hover {
    background: var(--color-border-strong);
    border-color: #f59e0b;
  }

  /* ── SECTIONS ── */
  .hp-section {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
  }

  .hp-section--surface {
    background: var(--color-bg-surface);
  }

  .hp-section-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .hp-section-sub {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin: 0 0 1.75rem;
    max-width: 60ch;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .hp-section-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .hp-text-link {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-accent);
    padding-bottom: 0.1rem;
  }

  .hp-text-link:hover {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  /* ── WHAT WE DO ── */
  .hp-decision-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .hp-decision-card {
    padding: 1.25rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-default);
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    background: var(--color-bg-page);
  }

  .hp-decision-label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.625rem;
  }

  .hp-decision-card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .hp-decision-footer {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0;
    max-width: 60ch;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ── WHO THIS IS FOR ── */
  .hp-audience-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .hp-audience-card {
    padding: 1.25rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-default);
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    background: var(--color-bg-page);
  }

  .hp-audience-type {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .hp-audience-card p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .hp-audience-footer {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0;
    max-width: 60ch;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ── FRAMEWORKS ── */
  .hp-fw-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .hp-fw-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.3rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.125rem;
    background: var(--color-bg-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-default);
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color 0.15s, box-shadow 0.15s;
  }

  .hp-fw-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-border-accent);
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.06);
  }

  .hp-fw-type {
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.07em;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .hp-fw-name {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .hp-fw-desc {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .hp-view-all {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-accent);
    padding-bottom: 0.1rem;
  }

  .hp-view-all:hover {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  /* ── OUTCOMES ── */
  .hp-outcomes-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .hp-outcome {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.375rem;
    background: var(--color-bg-surface);
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-border-accent);
  }

  .hp-outcome p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .hp-outcome p strong {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .hp-citation {
    display: block;
    font-style: normal;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    padding-top: 0.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  /* ── SERVICES CTA BANNER ── */
  .hp-cta-banner {
    background: var(--color-text-primary);
    padding: 3rem 0;
  }

  .hp-cta-inner {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 2rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .hp-cta-heading {
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-cta-text);
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
  }

  .hp-cta-sub {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    max-width: 48ch;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .hp-cta-services {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }

  .hp-cta-services li {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .hp-cta-services li strong {
    color: var(--color-cta-text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .hp-cta-entry {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .hp-cta-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .hp-btn-cta-outline {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.625rem 1.375rem;
    border: 1.5px solid var(--color-cta-border);
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-cta-text);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.15s;
  }

  .hp-btn-cta-outline:hover {
    background: rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.15);
  }

  /* ── FAQ ── */
  .hp-faq-container {
    max-width: 52rem;
  }

  .hp-faq-list {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .hp-faq-item {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-default);
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .hp-faq-q {
    display: block;
    padding: 0.875rem 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    user-select: none;
  }

  .hp-faq-q::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }

  .hp-faq-q::after {
    content: "+";
    float: right;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  details[open] .hp-faq-q::after {
    content: "−";
  }

  .hp-faq-a {
    padding: 0 1rem 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── DECISION RESOURCES ── */
  .hp-resources-table-wrap {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .hp-resources-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .hp-resources-table th {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0.625rem 1rem;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border-default);
  }

  .hp-resources-table td {
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    vertical-align: top;
  }

  .hp-resources-table td:first-child {
    white-space: nowrap;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

